‚òÄÔ∏è Global Forecast: Server-Side Rendered Weather AppA fast, server-side rendered (SSR) web application built with Node.js/Express that delivers real-time weather updates using the OpenWeatherMap API. The application enables users to search for any city and securely saves their previous search history using Firebase.‚ú® Features at a GlanceReal-time Data: Instantaneous and accurate weather data for any globally recognized city, powered by OpenWeatherMap.SSR Architecture: High performance and fast initial load times achieved through Server-Side Rendering with Express.js.Dynamic Views: Content dynamically generated on the server using EJS templating.Persistent History: Secure storage and retrieval of individual user search history managed via Firebase.Modern UI: Clean, fully responsive, and mobile-friendly user interface styled with Tailwind CSS.Smooth Interactions: Enhanced user experience with polished UI animations using the Motion library.üíª Tech StackCategoryTechnologyPurposeBackendNode.js (Express.js)Server-Side Rendering (SSR) and API handling.TemplatingEJSDynamic view generation on the server.Database/StorageFirebaseStoring persistent user search history.APIOpenWeatherMap APISource for real-time weather data.StylingTailwind CSSUtility-first CSS framework for responsive design.AnimationMotionHandling smooth UI transitions and animations.‚öôÔ∏è Installation & SetupPrerequisitesNode.js (LTS version recommended)An API key from OpenWeatherMapA Firebase Project configurationStepsClone the repository:git clone <repo-url>
cd weather-app
Install dependencies:npm install
Create .env file:Create a file named .env in the root directory and add your API keys and configuration details.WEATHER_API_KEY=your_openweathermap_api_key
# Provide the Firebase Web App config as a stringified JSON object:
FIREBASE_CONFIG='{"apiKey": "...", "authDomain": "...", "projectId": "..."}' 
Start the server:npm start
Access the application:Open your browser to http://localhost:3000.üöÄ UsageSearch: Enter any city name in the prominent search bar to instantly fetch and view current weather details.History: Review previously searched cities, which are saved and retrieved securely from your Firebase history.Experience: Enjoy a smooth, animated, and responsive design across desktop and mobile devices.üìö Key LearningsBuilding high-performance SSR applications with Express.js and EJS.Mastering the integration of third-party APIs (like OpenWeatherMap) for real-time data delivery.Implementing persistent data storage and retrieval using Firebase.Designing interactive and visually appealing interfaces using the combination of Tailwind CSS and Motion.Strengthening foundational understanding of HTML5, JavaScript, and CSS3 in a full-stack environment.üìÑ LicenseThis project is intended for personal learning and portfolio purposes.
